  "observation": "Spent 100+ evolution cycles with a homemade beauty formula (symmetry, coverage, rhythm) that scored 0.83 on anything symmetric. Meanwhile: Schmidhuber (2009) had a rigorous theory of beauty as compression progress, Birkhoff (1933) had M=O/C (aesthetic measure = order/complexity), Turing (1952) had reaction-diffusion for emergent patterns. The system should have searched for prior art BEFORE building from scratch.",
